sense.name: bring into common action, movement, or condition
sense.examples: The Project Manager will coordinate the setup of all new Compleat Book-Serv accounts. The United States will coordinate policy on Darfur with the United Nations. Finnair-1 agreed to coordinate flights , marketing and other functions with SAS.

sense.name: be complimentary with; act together smoothly
sense.examples: They coordinate perfectly with all of the other Fairytale Princess party items. The White Bamboo Blades coordinate with your choice of the Rustic Motor Housing or the White Motor Housing. Cartoons are relevant within the paper, and coordinate well with text for an effective result.
